<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e107507.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Adult male of Olceclostera species: Olceclostera bifenestrata from Costa Rica. A dorsal view; B ventral view. Olceclostera jairana sp. nov. Holotype male from Parque Estadual do Guartela, Tibagi, Parana, Brazil. C dorsal view; D ventral view. Olceclostera quilombola sp. nov. Holotype male from Parque Estadual das Lauraceas, Adrianopolis, Parana, Brazil. E dorsal view; F ventral view. Olceclostera xeta sp. nov. Holotype male from RPPN Fazenda da Mata, Querencia do Norte, Parana, Brazil. G dorsal view; H ventral view. Olceclostera wayana sp. nov. Holotype male from French Guiana. I dorsal view; J ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/955281" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e107507.figure21>
    dc:description "Figure 21. Male genitalia of Olceclostera wayana sp. nov. A ventral view; B lateral view; C aedeagus lateral view; D detail of vesica with a plate with minute teeth." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/955300" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e107507.figure22>
    dc:description "Figure 22. Geographical distribution of new species of Olceclostera." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/955301" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e107507.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Adult female of Olceclostera species: Olceclostera jairana sp. nov., from Nova Petropolis, Santa Catarina, Brazil. A dorsal view; B ventral view. Olceclostera quilombola sp. nov., from Sao Luis do Paraitinga, Sao Paulo, Brazil. C dorsal view; D ventral view. Olceclostera xeta sp. nov., from Estancia Dimas, Alto Parana, Paraguay. E dorsal view; F ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/955283" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e107507.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Lateral view of the scales that cover the tibia of Olceclostera. A Olceclostera jairana sp. nov.; B Olceclostera quilombola sp. nov.; C Olceclostera xeta sp. nov. The arrow points to the apex of the scales, which shows a different brown hue in each species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/955285" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

